# SANITATTOO Data Model Rules

You are acting as a senior backend/data engineer.

Your main responsibility is to keep the product catalog data clean, consistent, scalable and ready for a future migration to WooCommerce or Shopify.

The current project is a static React catalog, but the data must be modeled as if it could later be exported to CSV or imported into an ecommerce platform.

## Main responsibility

When working with catalog data, prioritize:

- Data consistency
- Future ecommerce compatibility
- Easy CSV export
- Clear product categorization
- Unique identifiers
- Clean slugs
- Numeric prices
- Reusable utility functions
- Avoiding duplicated logic

Do not focus on visual design in this rule. Visual design belongs to the frontend/design rule.

## Product source of truth

All product data must live in:

`src/data/products.js`

All category data must live in:

`src/data/categories.js`

Do not duplicate product data inside React components.

Do not hardcode product cards manually.

## Required product fields

Every product must include:

- `id`
- `sku`
- `name`
- `slug`
- `category`
- `categoryLabel`
- `price`
- `currency`
- `unit`
- `image`
- `alt`
- `shortDescription`
- `description`
- `tags`
- `featured`
- `offer`
- `active`

Recommended base shape:

```js
{
  id: "",
  sku: "",
  name: "",
  slug: "",
  category: "",
  categoryLabel: "",
  price: null,
  currency: "EUR",
  unit: "",
  image: "",
  alt: "",
  shortDescription: "",
  description: "",
  tags: [],
  featured: false,
  offer: false,
  active: true
}
```

## Optional product fields

Products may include:

- `variants`
- `merchandisingFeatured`
- `badge`
- `stockStatus`
- `format`
- `size`
- `color`
- `material`
- `notes`

Use optional fields only when they add real value.

Do not add random fields without a clear reason.

## Price rules

Prices must always be numbers.

Correct:

```js
price: 9
```

Incorrect:

```js
price: "9€"
```

If the product does not have a defined price yet, use:

```js
price: null
```

The currency must be stored separately:

```js
currency: "EUR"
```

Never include the euro symbol inside the price value.

## SKU rules

Every SKU must be unique.

Use the prefix:

`SAN-`

Examples:

- `SAN-FILM-NEGRO-50X120`
- `SAN-GUANTES-NITRILO-NEGRO-M`
- `SAN-MERCH-CAMISETA-NEGRA`

Do not generate duplicate SKUs.

Do not use spaces, accents or special symbols in SKUs.

## Slug rules

Slugs must be:

- lowercase
- URL-safe
- without accents
- without spaces
- separated by hyphens

Correct:

`guantes-nitrilo-negro`

Incorrect:

- `Guantes Nitrilo Negro`
- `guantes_nitrilo_negro`
- `guantes-nitrílo-negro`

## Category rules

Allowed category keys:

- `proteccion-higiene`
- `desinfeccion-limpieza`
- `consumibles`
- `mobiliario-camilla`
- `stencil-preparacion`
- `aftercare`
- `merchandising`

Do not create new categories unless explicitly requested.

Each category must have:

```js
{
  id: "",
  name: "",
  description: ""
}
```

Category IDs must match the product `category` field.

## Variant rules

If a product has multiple sizes, colors, formats or units, prefer using a `variants` array.

Example:

```js
variants: [
  {
    label: "30x300",
    price: 8,
    sku: "SAN-FILM-TRANSPARENTE-30X300"
  },
  {
    label: "45x300",
    price: 12,
    sku: "SAN-FILM-TRANSPARENTE-45X300"
  }
]
```

Use separate products only when the item is clearly independent.

Do not create unnecessary duplicate products for small variations.

## Featured and merchandising logic

Use:

```js
featured: true
```

for products that should appear in the homepage featured products preview.

Use:

```js
category: "merchandising"
```

for merchandising products.

Use:

```js
merchandisingFeatured: true
```

for merchandising products that should appear in the homepage merchandising preview.

The homepage must not render the full catalog.

## Offers logic

Use:

```js
offer: true
```

for products that should appear on the `/ofertas` page.

If a product is not on offer, use:

```js
offer: false
```

## Active products

Use:

```js
active: true
```

for products visible on the website.

Use:

```js
active: false
```

for products that should remain in the data file but not appear in public listings.

Do not delete inactive products unless explicitly requested.

## Image rules

Product images should use this path pattern when real product images exist:

`/images/productos/product-name.webp`

If real product images are not available yet, use placeholder paths or generic placeholders.

Example:

```js
image: "/images/placeholders/product-placeholder.webp"
```

Every product must include meaningful alt text.

Example:

```js
alt: "Film negro para protección en estudio de tatuaje"
```

Do not leave alt text empty.

## Placeholder image behavior

Until real images are added to the project, use placeholder or generic image references.

Do not block development because final images are missing.

Do not invent exact product photography filenames unless the product image exists.

Prefer this temporary fallback:

```js
image: "/images/placeholders/product-placeholder.webp"
```

## Utility rules

Reusable logic must go inside:

`src/utils/`

Useful utilities may include:

- `formatPrice.js`
- `whatsapp.js`
- `filterProducts.js`
- `slugify.js`

Do not duplicate WhatsApp URL generation across components.

Do not duplicate price formatting across components.

## CSV/export compatibility

When editing product data, keep future WooCommerce or Shopify export in mind.

Avoid deeply nested structures unless necessary.

Avoid mixing display text and raw data.

Prefer clean fields that can map to CSV columns:

- `name`
- `sku`
- `slug`
- `category`
- `price`
- `currency`
- `description`
- `shortDescription`
- `image`
- `tags`
- `active`

## Do not implement

Do not implement:

- backend
- database
- authentication
- cart
- checkout
- payment gateway
- admin panel
- stock management system

This project is currently a static catalog and lead generation website.
